WEBVTT

00:00.135 --> 00:05.004
♪♪

00:05.004 --> 00:06.732
TRAY: <i>What does it mean to be a man?</i>

00:07.948 --> 00:09.285
<i>Being a man used to mean</i>

00:09.286 --> 00:11.237
<i>being able to handle your business.</i>

00:12.239 --> 00:13.391
<i>A man don't cry.</i>

00:14.216 --> 00:15.775
<i>A man don't ask for help.</i>

00:16.226 --> 00:18.188
<i>A man don't even go to the doctor.</i>

00:18.680 --> 00:20.780
<i>Catch me if you can, Diabetes!</i>

00:20.782 --> 00:21.776
[LAUGHS]

00:22.723 --> 00:25.867
<i>But now in this present
time, rules are different.</i>

00:26.738 --> 00:28.571
<i>Now, a man can be anything he wants.</i>

00:28.572 --> 00:30.004
<i>Hell, he can even be a woman,</i>

00:30.006 --> 00:31.916
<i>like the dude on the Wheaties box.</i>

00:33.894 --> 00:36.001
<i>Sometimes, it's like
there's no rules at all.</i>

00:36.213 --> 00:37.812
♪♪

00:38.351 --> 00:42.009
<i>I don't know if that makes
things easier or harder.</i>

00:43.757 --> 00:46.009
♪♪

00:46.009 --> 00:48.343
It's a mad house!

00:48.346 --> 00:51.148
A mad house!

00:57.768 --> 00:59.544
JAYBIRD: I keep telling y'all. I'm wild.

00:59.544 --> 01:00.875
Don't let these curls fool you.

01:00.875 --> 01:02.574
I'm out of my mind crazy, bruh.

01:02.827 --> 01:04.994
Stole somebody's Citi
Bike, never returned it.

01:04.995 --> 01:06.563
FELONY: Okay, okay. You think that's bad?

01:06.883 --> 01:07.877
Yo, one time,

01:07.877 --> 01:10.074
I stole a horse and
buggy from Central Park.

01:10.074 --> 01:11.098
How you do that?

01:11.098 --> 01:12.740
I caught the coachman slipping.

01:12.866 --> 01:15.137
He was coming out of the
grocery with a handful of bags.

01:15.245 --> 01:16.754
I hemmed him up in the alley,

01:16.754 --> 01:18.269
got him for one of them avocados,

01:18.269 --> 01:19.535
snatched his hat and coat,

01:20.188 --> 01:21.454
horse never knew the difference.

01:21.852 --> 01:24.814
I made like $88 before 5-0 rode me down.

01:24.814 --> 01:27.085
Not to be impressed by
anything you did wrong,

01:27.291 --> 01:28.523
but I'm impressed.

01:28.526 --> 01:29.892
- Thank you.
- Fool?!

01:30.278 --> 01:31.868
You know you can't tame no horse!

01:31.963 --> 01:32.900
Stop lying!

01:32.900 --> 01:34.066
Close the door!

01:34.068 --> 01:35.803
Okay, I hear your horse thievery,

01:35.936 --> 01:37.803
and I up you the Statue of Liberty.

01:37.805 --> 01:38.971
- Word?
- Word.

01:38.973 --> 01:40.873
Now, this is before 9/11,

01:40.875 --> 01:42.890
so there weren't no
security up in that bitch.

01:42.890 --> 01:45.093
Now, my boy and I, we
bum-rushed the statue,

01:45.403 --> 01:48.438
and he drops every tourist
from the panties down,

01:48.556 --> 01:50.926
and I rob everybody

01:50.951 --> 01:53.444
from the tits to the torch.

01:53.445 --> 01:55.778
TRAY: That might be the
grimiest shit I've ever heard.

01:55.780 --> 01:58.511
'Cause robbing the Statue of
Liberty is just un-American.

02:00.171 --> 02:01.584
One time I killed a pigeon.

02:01.586 --> 02:03.486
TRAY: Killing a pigeon's
definitely messed up,

02:03.488 --> 02:05.542
- but I think Big Country takes the cake.
- [DOOR OPENS]

02:05.717 --> 02:07.950
[LAUGHS] Big Country always take the cake,

02:07.992 --> 02:09.011
'cause he fat.

02:09.013 --> 02:10.779
[LAUGHS]

02:10.781 --> 02:12.247
Come on, y'all got to laugh at that one.

02:12.249 --> 02:13.248
That's funny.

02:13.250 --> 02:14.716
[FAKE LAUGHTER]

02:14.718 --> 02:16.251
[LAUGHS]

02:16.253 --> 02:17.520
[SIGHS]

02:18.231 --> 02:19.321
BIG COUNTRY: Yo, Tray?

02:20.312 --> 02:21.916
What's the wildest thing you ever done?

02:21.916 --> 02:22.996
Who, me?

02:23.321 --> 02:24.287
[SIGHS]

02:24.288 --> 02:25.279
Ah, man.

02:25.779 --> 02:27.668
- All right, so one time...
- [CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

02:29.593 --> 02:30.761
It's my son.

02:32.129 --> 02:33.336
Shahzad!

02:33.731 --> 02:35.407
What's up, boy-boy?

02:35.407 --> 02:36.498
Holla at me.

02:36.500 --> 02:37.525
SHAHZAD: <i>Hey, Tray?</i>

02:37.701 --> 02:39.034
<i>Can you come to my school?</i>

02:39.036 --> 02:40.660
You want me to come to your school?

02:40.727 --> 02:42.040
<i>Yeah. Can you?</i>

02:42.673 --> 02:44.706
Sure. No doubt.

02:44.708 --> 02:46.441
- <i>Thanks, Tray.</i>
- All right.

02:46.581 --> 02:47.660
All right, cool.

02:47.745 --> 02:50.345
♪♪

02:50.347 --> 02:51.379
Gentlemen...

02:51.381 --> 02:52.627
[SIGHS]

02:52.850 --> 02:54.367
...my son needs me.

02:54.367 --> 02:57.120
- Congrats, Tray. Good for you.
- JAYBIRD: Impressive, man.

02:57.145 --> 02:58.778
Your boy had three parents to choose from

02:58.780 --> 02:59.979
and he called you.

02:59.981 --> 03:01.948
It's that biological connection.

03:01.950 --> 03:05.133
Gentlemen, this will be my finest

03:06.188 --> 03:07.156
hour.

03:07.889 --> 03:10.390
[APPLAUSE]

03:14.396 --> 03:15.849
- Shahzad?! 
- [KNOCKS ON DOOR]

03:16.192 --> 03:17.258
Oh.

03:17.744 --> 03:19.432
You must be Mr. Barker.

03:19.434 --> 03:20.747
Well, I must be.

03:20.936 --> 03:22.335
What happened, Shahzad?

03:22.335 --> 03:24.202
Eh, why don't you take a seat, Mr. Barker?

03:25.839 --> 03:27.639
So, Shahzad was caught with a weapon

03:27.641 --> 03:29.223
in school today.

03:29.442 --> 03:31.380
What?! A weapon?

03:31.427 --> 03:32.710
You brought a weapon to school?

03:32.712 --> 03:33.926
You brought a gun to school?

03:34.037 --> 03:35.048
Well...

03:37.063 --> 03:38.255
Nunchucks?

03:38.625 --> 03:39.824
Those ain't no weapons.

03:39.826 --> 03:41.001
Oh, well, technically, they are.

03:41.001 --> 03:42.393
Well, if you could call that a weapon,

03:42.395 --> 03:43.527
you could call anything a weapon.

03:43.529 --> 03:44.872
But it's literally a weapon.

03:45.064 --> 03:46.350
Well, I call this a weapon.

03:46.350 --> 03:48.206
I mean, this heavy as shit.

03:48.447 --> 03:50.310
You could bash somebody's brains in

03:50.310 --> 03:51.515
if you wanted to.

03:51.517 --> 03:52.724
What is this thing?

03:52.724 --> 03:54.696
It's a hole puncher. A hole puncher?

03:54.748 --> 03:56.949
It could punch a hole in
somebody's head, maybe.

03:56.951 --> 03:58.403
- [LAUGHS] Sir, I...
- [DESK RATTLES]

03:58.403 --> 03:59.449
And this...

03:59.753 --> 04:01.061
This is a shank.

04:01.061 --> 04:03.261
- That's a letter opener.
- A letter opener?

04:03.263 --> 04:04.629
More like a stomach opener. Uh...

04:04.631 --> 04:06.475
You know the damage you could do with this

04:06.475 --> 04:07.555
on a prison yard?

04:07.555 --> 04:08.687
- [GRUNTING]
- Sir?

04:08.689 --> 04:10.122
Okay, Mr. Barker? [LAUGHS]

04:10.124 --> 04:11.256
Those nunchucks look like

04:11.258 --> 04:13.093
some damn "Ninja Turtle" toys.

04:13.253 --> 04:16.028
Them 'chucks is probably the
safest thing in this room.

04:16.029 --> 04:18.130
- Okay, this is absurd.
- Absurd?

04:18.314 --> 04:20.390
What's absurd is you
trying to railroad my son

04:20.390 --> 04:21.778
on some bullshit.

04:21.968 --> 04:23.653
Did you see him use that weapon?

04:23.907 --> 04:26.544
- Well, no, I didn't see him use them.
- There you go.

04:26.569 --> 04:28.335
The burden of proof is on you.

04:28.338 --> 04:30.302
Or do you just want to
see another black man

04:30.302 --> 04:31.368
in the penal system?

04:31.370 --> 04:32.533
Of course not.

04:33.238 --> 04:35.004
Shahzad is a wonderful student.

04:35.006 --> 04:36.706
He... he's never been a problem before.

04:36.859 --> 04:39.521
But I'm afraid I am gonna
have to dismiss him...

04:41.046 --> 04:42.612
...for the rest of the afternoon.

04:42.971 --> 04:45.047
You know, maybe you can explain to him

04:45.047 --> 04:46.447
why bringing something
like this into school

04:46.449 --> 04:48.182
is inappropriate.

04:48.184 --> 04:50.851
Madam, I will do just that.

04:50.853 --> 04:52.419
And thank you for your understanding

04:52.421 --> 04:53.546
on this matter.

04:54.045 --> 04:55.093
Shahzad?

04:56.793 --> 04:57.880
Come.

04:57.880 --> 04:59.418
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

05:02.218 --> 05:04.339
- [DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]
- [SIGHS]

05:04.771 --> 05:05.855
Yo, Shahzad?

05:06.456 --> 05:07.789
You getting in trouble at school?

05:07.791 --> 05:09.606
Are you trying to discipline me now?

05:09.793 --> 05:11.726
[LAUGHS] I'm not disciplining you.

05:12.014 --> 05:13.594
The school is disciplining you.

05:13.594 --> 05:15.631
You the one that got
suspended by your teacher.

05:15.896 --> 05:18.715
- That was a guidance counselor.
- Whoever it is.

05:18.938 --> 05:20.332
If you gonna call me out here,

05:20.334 --> 05:22.145
why you not respecting me as a parent?

05:23.228 --> 05:25.388
Oh. You trying to be my father now?

05:26.065 --> 05:27.119
Shahzad?

05:28.475 --> 05:29.566
Please don't play me.

05:29.568 --> 05:31.168
Look, I didn't call Mom or Dad,

05:31.170 --> 05:32.676
because I didn't want a lecture, Tray,

05:32.756 --> 05:34.376
but it looks like I'm gonna get one anyway.

05:34.376 --> 05:35.438
You damn right.

05:35.463 --> 05:37.055
If you gonna get me involved in this,

05:37.055 --> 05:38.554
let me know what's going on.

05:38.922 --> 05:41.112
Or I get your mother involved

05:41.232 --> 05:42.517
and she can deal with it.

05:42.748 --> 05:44.481
And you know you don't want that.

05:44.483 --> 05:46.049
What? You don't rat.

05:46.257 --> 05:47.584
That's your whole thing.

05:49.035 --> 05:52.319
I'll rat your little ass out
like Sammy the Bull did Gotti.

05:52.691 --> 05:53.957
Start singing.

05:53.959 --> 05:56.094
[CHUCKLES] Fine.

05:56.395 --> 06:01.164
♪♪

06:01.449 --> 06:02.815
- Here you go, sir.
- Thank you.

06:02.817 --> 06:04.362
- You're welcome.
- Don't I get one?

06:05.039 --> 06:06.095
Hell, no.

06:06.991 --> 06:08.935
You brought nunchucks to school, man.

06:09.333 --> 06:11.479
Now, fess up. Why you
bring a weapon to school?

06:11.593 --> 06:13.261
You said nunchucks aren't a weapon.

06:13.496 --> 06:14.813
Of course, they're weapons.

06:14.813 --> 06:16.793
You ever seen "Enter the
Dragon" with Bruce Lee?

06:16.892 --> 06:19.280
He could take out a
whole room full of motherfuckers

06:19.280 --> 06:20.479
with them nunchucks.

06:21.055 --> 06:22.421
- Now, talk.
- [SIGHS]

06:22.423 --> 06:24.189
I've been having trouble
at school, all right?

06:24.191 --> 06:26.316
- You mean bullying?
- This kid named Noah.

06:26.547 --> 06:27.846
He's huge, Tray.

06:28.095 --> 06:30.818
He's fat and he has a pointy head.

06:30.818 --> 06:31.851
Noah?

06:32.180 --> 06:33.724
[LAUGHS]

06:33.921 --> 06:35.721
You got beef with a dude named Noah?

06:36.207 --> 06:38.491
If you're gonna make fun
of me, just forget about it.

06:38.492 --> 06:41.462
Oh, hey, it's okay. It's okay.

06:41.796 --> 06:42.889
I ain't mean to laugh, man.

06:43.146 --> 06:44.412
It's not your fault.

06:44.414 --> 06:45.480
It's just the way you were raised, man.

06:45.482 --> 06:46.748
They got you all book-smart,

06:46.750 --> 06:48.208
and you ain't got no street-smarts.

06:48.629 --> 06:50.318
A'ight? You need to learn

06:50.320 --> 06:52.053
how to handle yourself
like a man out here, man,

06:52.055 --> 06:53.780
'cause these streets are tough.

06:54.091 --> 06:55.765
Guess who poured the concrete?

06:56.193 --> 06:57.526
That's where I come in.

06:57.916 --> 06:59.965
Now, me and you gonna
have a day together, man.

07:00.263 --> 07:01.741
You could consider this

07:02.299 --> 07:04.432
your Tray-ning Day.

07:04.695 --> 07:05.661
Mmm.

07:07.167 --> 07:10.421
Come on, guys, we got zero.
You've given me nothing.

07:10.524 --> 07:13.151
Nothing. Anything? You
got anything, please?

07:13.205 --> 07:15.572
- Well, what about Canada, you know?
- What about it?

07:15.574 --> 07:16.873
Yeah, we could have fun with it.

07:16.875 --> 07:18.441
Poutine, ketchup potato chips.

07:18.443 --> 07:19.876
- Uh-huh.
- It'd be very tongue-in-cheek.

07:19.878 --> 07:21.396
- Be very tongue-in-cheek, yeah.
- Yeah.

07:21.421 --> 07:23.159
If I pitch that to Anthony,
it's gonna be foot-in-ass.

07:23.159 --> 07:24.157
Come on.

07:24.182 --> 07:26.327
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

07:26.739 --> 07:28.839
- Yeah?
- WOMAN: <i>Hi, is this Josh Birkeland?</i>

07:28.841 --> 07:30.741
- Speaking.
- <i>This is The Rothman School.</i>

07:30.743 --> 07:32.910
<i>We're gonna need you to
come down here right away.</i>

07:32.912 --> 07:34.779
- <i>We have a little situation.</i>
- Oh, brother.

07:34.781 --> 07:37.529
Okay. Yeah, I'm at work, but I'll, uh...

07:37.530 --> 07:38.696
I'll be right there.

07:38.698 --> 07:40.020
See you soon.

07:41.299 --> 07:44.467
Amira, your dad's gonna be here soon.

07:44.469 --> 07:46.846
Noah, you okay?

07:47.326 --> 07:48.928
No? Hmm.

07:49.340 --> 07:50.706
Okay. That's fair.

07:51.080 --> 07:52.608
JOSH: So, you were fighting at school

07:52.610 --> 07:54.577
and Shahzad got sent home for nunchucks

07:54.579 --> 07:56.279
and then got picked up by Tray?

07:56.281 --> 07:57.413
What is happening?

07:57.415 --> 07:58.581
I mean, tell me everything,

07:58.583 --> 07:59.949
and start from the beginning.

07:59.951 --> 08:02.551
Okay, well, Noah's been picking on 'Zad...

08:02.553 --> 08:04.086
- Great.
- ...and he's scared to fight him,

08:04.088 --> 08:05.821
so he brought nunchucks to protect himself,

08:05.823 --> 08:07.449
got caught with the
nunchucks and got sent home.

08:07.474 --> 08:08.491
There you go.

08:08.493 --> 08:10.126
Okay, so you beat up this Noah

08:10.128 --> 08:11.560
as, like, an act of revenge?

08:11.562 --> 08:13.562
No, I beat up Noah,
'cause he's a punk, okay?

08:13.564 --> 08:14.978
He needed to get beat up.

08:14.979 --> 08:16.766
No. If you kids have a problem at school,

08:16.768 --> 08:18.274
you come to me or you go to your mother.

08:18.275 --> 08:20.042
We don't go around hitting people.

08:21.147 --> 08:22.513
Tell you and Mom?

08:23.263 --> 08:24.279
Oh, okay.

08:24.281 --> 08:25.447
Yeah, I'll tell you and Mom,

08:25.449 --> 08:26.582
'cause you guys will flip out,

08:26.584 --> 08:27.951
just like you're doing right now.

08:27.951 --> 08:29.517
Look, it's fine. I handled it.

08:29.519 --> 08:30.669
No, you didn't handle it.

08:30.669 --> 08:32.268
You got booted from school for three days.

08:32.270 --> 08:33.302
That's not handling it.

08:33.304 --> 08:34.736
Yeah, totally worth it.

08:34.739 --> 08:36.792
Hey, we'll see how totally worth it is

08:36.817 --> 08:38.073
when I tell your mother.

08:43.885 --> 08:45.148
[ENGINE STARTS]

08:45.933 --> 08:48.532
- You're really gonna tell Mom?
- Absolutely, yeah.

08:48.564 --> 08:50.942
This is exactly why I
didn't want to call you.

08:51.405 --> 08:52.671
- Oh, really?
- Yeah, really.

08:52.673 --> 08:54.372
Shahzad didn't call you, either.

08:54.374 --> 08:55.487
He called Tray.

08:55.487 --> 08:56.886
Tray's cool.

08:56.888 --> 08:58.688
[SIGHS] You guys aren't.

08:58.690 --> 09:00.924
♪♪

09:00.926 --> 09:03.165
- I am cool.
- Yeah.

09:03.190 --> 09:04.154
Right.

09:05.430 --> 09:06.529
I am.

09:06.531 --> 09:09.799
♪♪

09:09.801 --> 09:11.069
[SIGHS]

09:11.603 --> 09:12.750
Stupid thing.

09:13.105 --> 09:14.971
♪♪

09:14.973 --> 09:16.639
Hi, and welcome to Grundle's.

09:16.641 --> 09:18.308
Oh. Tray, it's you.

09:18.310 --> 09:20.844
You didn't recognize me with my son, huh?

09:20.846 --> 09:22.178
No, I didn't.

09:22.180 --> 09:23.630
That's your son? [LAUGHS]

09:23.631 --> 09:26.698
Shahzad, this is my coworker Elizabeth.

09:26.881 --> 09:28.086
Um, I'm actually his manager.

09:28.111 --> 09:29.148
I'm his boss.

09:29.173 --> 09:30.673
But it's nice to meet you, Shahzad.

09:30.675 --> 09:32.108
Hi, nice to meet you.

09:32.418 --> 09:34.822
Oh. He seems so nice and articulate.

09:34.847 --> 09:36.367
He seems different than you.

09:36.367 --> 09:37.700
Well, he's his own man.

09:37.717 --> 09:39.478
Look, I came to pick up my check.

09:39.503 --> 09:41.270
Oh, well, checks get mailed on Tuesday.

09:41.272 --> 09:42.705
Yeah, but they get cut on Monday.

09:42.707 --> 09:43.939
You don't have to mail mine.

09:43.941 --> 09:45.174
Tray, we can't release them early.

09:45.520 --> 09:47.186
Is Wavy back...? Wavy?!

09:47.188 --> 09:48.487
Hang on, I'll call him.

09:48.489 --> 09:50.523
Wavy?! Tray's here!

09:50.525 --> 09:51.874
WAVY: Stack that in the corner.

09:51.996 --> 09:53.125
What up, baby boy?

09:53.127 --> 09:54.510
Yo, Wavy. I need my check.

09:54.510 --> 09:56.510
I'm hanging out with my
son today, and I'm broke.

09:56.513 --> 09:57.695
This your son?

09:57.935 --> 09:59.706
Man, that boy look just like you,

09:59.731 --> 10:00.963
except he more handsome.

10:01.102 --> 10:03.359
Must be Shay's fine-ass genes.

10:03.359 --> 10:05.058
Uh, yeah, the checks came this morning.

10:05.060 --> 10:06.326
- Let me grab one for you.
- ELIZABETH: Oh, no, no, wait, wait.

10:06.328 --> 10:07.628
Just want to remind you,

10:07.630 --> 10:09.272
we're not allowed to release checks early.

10:09.273 --> 10:11.502
[SIGHS] Right. Right.

10:11.815 --> 10:13.930
We could get in a lot of
trouble from corporate, Tray.

10:13.930 --> 10:15.597
Yeah, but how they gonna find out, though?

10:15.600 --> 10:16.699
WAVY: Here we are.

10:16.701 --> 10:19.156
I'll advance you a couple dollars,

10:19.326 --> 10:20.766
some walk-around money.

10:20.966 --> 10:22.166
Nice to meet you, young man.

10:22.191 --> 10:23.208
Nice to meet you.

10:23.208 --> 10:24.307
- WAVY: You have a good day.
- You, too.

10:24.309 --> 10:25.948
- Thanks a lot, homey.
- Any time.

10:28.117 --> 10:29.130
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:29.280 --> 10:33.025
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

10:35.399 --> 10:36.908
- Hi.
- Welcome to Grundle's!

10:37.252 --> 10:39.055
TRAY: This what my father did for me.

10:39.679 --> 10:41.498
Taught me how to handle myself.

10:42.557 --> 10:44.724
Buying this was a waste of money, Tray.

10:44.726 --> 10:47.511
- Yo, take your glasses off, man.
- This is dumb.

10:47.829 --> 10:49.062
What the [BLEEP]?!

10:49.064 --> 10:50.463
Tray, you almost broke my glasses!

10:50.465 --> 10:52.098
Well, that's why I told
you to take 'em off!

10:52.413 --> 10:54.494
